1️⃣ SEQUENCE
🔹 PL/SQL Meaning:

Auto-generate unique IDs.

🔹 In YOUR Project:
_id: ObjectId("...")


MongoDB automatically generates _id.

🔹 HOW YOU WRITE IN DOCUMENT:

MongoDB ObjectId works like a sequence and auto-generates unique Employee IDs.

📌 Marks-worthy point
2️⃣ FUNCTION
🔹 PL/SQL Meaning:

Return a calculated value.

🔹 In YOUR Project:

We will create JS functions in:

utils/employeeFunctions.js

Example:
exports.calculateAge = (dob) => {
  const diff = Date.now() - new Date(dob).getTime();
  return Math.floor(diff / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 365));
};

exports.calculateExperience = (joiningDate) => {
  const diff = Date.now() - new Date(joiningDate).getTime();
  return Math.floor(diff / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 365));
};


✔ Age
✔ Experience

🔹 Used when?

When employee is fetched

When showing frontend table

📌 THIS COUNTS AS FUNCTION

3️⃣ PROCEDURE (IN parameter)
🔹 PL/SQL Meaning:

Performs action, no return value.

🔹 In YOUR Project:

Controller functions like:

createEmployee(req, res)


They:

Take input

Insert into DB

Do not return value, only status

📌 Controller = Procedure

4️⃣ CURSOR
🔹 PL/SQL Meaning:

Fetch records one-by-one or as loop.

🔹 In YOUR Project:
Employee.find()


OR in frontend:

employees.forEach(emp => { ... });


This is exactly cursor looping.

📌 Write this clearly in documentation:

Fetching employee records and looping through them using JavaScript acts as cursor functionality.

5️⃣ EXCEPTION HANDLING
🔹 PL/SQL Meaning:

Handle runtime errors.

🔹 In YOUR Project:
try {
  ...
} catch (error) {
  res.status(400).json({ message: error.message });
}


Examples:

Duplicate email

Invalid departmentId

Missing fields

📌 Direct mapping

6️⃣ TRIGGER
🔹 PL/SQL Meaning:

Auto action on INSERT / DELETE.

🔹 In YOUR Project:

We simulate trigger using Mongoose middleware.

Example:
employeeSchema.pre("save", function(next) {
  console.log("Employee record is being created");
  next();
});


OR:

Auto createdAt

Auto updatedAt

📌 THIS IS TRIGGER LOGIC

7️⃣ PACKAGE
🔹 PL/SQL Meaning:

Group procedures & functions.

🔹 In YOUR Project:
utils/employeeFunctions.js
controllers/employeeController.js


Grouped logic = Package

📌 Write:

JavaScript modules act as packages grouping related functions.